parameters:
Would you like to view the event? The Timid Customer's
Hidden Potential

\nc<Employee>That customer has been loitering around for a while now...
Should we kick them out?

\bustMsgExp[2, 1]\nc<Senpai>Seems like a hopeless coward. It would be a shame to throw
them out.

\bustMsgExp[2, 0]\nc<Senpai>Yes. That type of customer, once they get a taste, they turn
into splendid... I mean, regulars.

\nc<Employee>I see. But when I tried to recommend a course earlier, they
ran away.
\nc<Senpai>You can't approach them by calling out.

\nc<Employee>Then what should we do? Normally, even the succubi dislike
that type of customer...

\nc<Senpai>It's fine. This is exactly the time for us to show our ace
in the hole.

\nc<Senpai>Saki, you're free right now, aren't you? Come here for a
second.
\nc<Senpai>Do you see that customer over there?
\nc<Saki>They seem... incredibly suspicious in their behavior.

\nc<Senpai>Right? That customer seems to be an evaluator for the Sexure
Guide.

\nc<Senpai>Yes. You've heard about it, haven't you? The one-star, two-
star ratings...

\nc<Saki>Isn't that something for restaurants? I had no idea it
existed in the succubus industry too...(I guess it's not too
strange to have something like that... maybe?)

\nc<Senpai>If we don't get a Sexure rating this time, our company might
be in danger. Saki, can I leave it to you?

\nc<Saki>Eh, that's too much for me! If it's like that, Senpai, you
should personally attend to them...

\nc<Senpai>If I go out there directly, they'll know it's not just
regular hospitality.

\nc<Saki>Right... A Sexure Guide evaluator committee. What should I
do...

\nc<Senpai>Just act as usual but be more proactive in inviting the
customer this time.
\nc<Senpai>Oh, and if it goes well, you might even get some paid leave.

\nc<Employee>Do we really need to concoct such a strange lie like the
Sexure Guide?

\nc<Senpai>Saki performs better with a bit of pressure on her.
Besides... it's funny that she actually believes such a
story.

\bustMsgExp[1, 3]\bustMoveTo[1, 1300, 720, 30]\nc<Saki>Hello. Um, would you like to see a room that suits your
taste...

\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>(Wow, they ran away just from being spoken to... They're
very wary. Are they pretending to be a nuisance customer?)
\bustMsgExp[1, 3]\n<Saki>(But I can't give up on the chance for paid leave!)

\nc<Saki>(Oh no, this is so embarrassing. But I was told to invite
them proactively... Huh? Are they coming this way?)

\nc<Saki>(I'm being watched so intently... Ahh, this outfit is
embarrassing but nothing is showing, right?)

\nc<Senpai>What is that idiot doing... No, maybe she's just right for
an idiot like that customer.
\nc<>The customer is staring intently at Saki's body.
\nc<Saki>(It worked! But doing it in the hallway is a bit...)

\nc<Saki>Ah, dear customer, I apologize. Touching in the hallway is
not allowed. Would you like to register as a member?
\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>More work has piled up again...
